Reserve Judge Neal Nettesheim presiding for Branch IV:

Cases 16CF25, 16CF82, 16CT105 called together at 2:22pm [mo]
Defendant Terri M Willingham in court with Attorney Whitney Hagemann.   ADA Monica Hall appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

As to Case 16CT105:
Maximum penalties recited; Constitutional rights reviewed; plea of " NO CONTEST " entered on Count #1
On Motion of the State, the Court reads-in and dismisses Count #2.

As to Cases 16CF25 and 16CF82:
Maximum penalties recited; Constitutional rights reviewed; plea of " NO CONTEST " entered on Case 16CF25
On Motion of the State, the Court reads in and dismisses Case 16CF82

As to All Cases: 
factual basis stipulated; the Court accepts the plea, finds Defendant guilty, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.

Sentencing arguments given by Counsel

On Case 16CT105, Count #1, the Court sentences the Defendant to 5 months in the Jefferson County jail, with Huber, consecutive. The Court STAYS this sentence and places the Defendant on Probation for 2 year, withs conditions:

 --To serve  20 days   in the Jefferson County Jail, with Huber/work release privileges; to commence FORTHWITH, followed immediately by 40  days on SCRAM X ("good time" credit to be applied to both components of order) Release shall be allowed for AA and/or NA meetings. Defendant not to be released from jail until SCRAM X device installed. 
--Comply with ALL conditions of Jefferson County Alcohol Treatment Court
--absolute sobriety
--no possession or consumption of alcohol
--no possession or consumption of controlled substances without a valid prescription 
--take all prescriptions as prescribed
--no presence in bars, taverns or liquor stores
--no operation of a motor vehicle without a valid Driver's License and Agent Approval
--any assessment, treatment or counseling as required by the Agent
--To pay fine of $630 + costs
--to pay $56.74 in blood testing fees to JCSO

The Court orders outright: 
--Revocation of drivers license for 27 months
--AODA assessment and follow through with recommended treatment
--Victim impact panel attendance
--Ignition Interlock Device required on any vehicle driven by the Defendant for a 27 month period  
--provide DNA sample
--Judgement of Conviction to indicate "ALCOHOL TREATMENT COURT PARTICIPANT"

On Case 16CF25 the Court withholds sentence, and places Defendant on Probation for 2 year, with all conditions as ordered in 16CT105 with the exception of the jail component(no jail ordered on Case 16CF25) and fine and blood draw fees (16CF25 has own statutory costs)  and:
--to compete a certified Batterers' Intervention programming
--to pay statutory costs

2 days credit on 16CF25
2 days credit on 16CT105

The Defendant is to comply with all SCRAM Program conditions of participation including payment of program costs and fees. 
- No alcohol possession or ingestion 
- No presence in bars, taverns or liquor stores
- No operation of a motor vehicle without a valid d.l.
